{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"111f62ab-730e-4f4b-b1e7-9b56c8c02d37","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** – upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n\n2. **Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** – it's the VSTest entry point and is no longer needed.\n\n3. **Add the new runner package:**\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n   *(v5 of the adapter may pull this transitively; check your restore output.)*\n\n4. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # works with the property above\n   # or directly:\n   dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n   ```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- The test executable is now a standalone app (has its own `Main`).\n- CLI flags differ from VSTest (`--filter` → `--treenode-filter`, etc.).\n- Extensions (loggers, code coverage) are now opt-in NuGet packages under `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.*`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cbf3c8a9-d9ce-41db-ac1f-674cf0978e8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":395,"requestId":"285E:6BBC1:158A709:16F0815:6A045FC9"},"id":"79be549a-5104-4b39-8819-0f7f8080cac5","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:17.507Z","parentId":"a230ddc7-6cf2-43e2-b4cd-954a0e9acf2f"}
